    "caption": "The ancient steppe runner with the most unusual nose on four legs.",
    "shortDescription": "The saiga antelope has a large, droopy, almost trunk-like nose that looks like no other animal's face. That strange nose is a superpower: in summer it filters out the clouds of dust kicked up by stampeding herds, and in winter it warms and humidifies freezing air before it reaches the lungs. Fun fact: Saiga can sprint at over eighty kilometres per hour across the open steppe."
